00:12:37.580 --> 00:12:42.690
Seeing cute girls really cheers me up.

252
00:12:43.360 --> 00:12:48.250
But the girls in these games 
are more than just cute.

253
00:12:48.720 --> 00:12:52.580
They cry, laugh, face lots of worries,

254
00:12:53.130 --> 00:12:56.090
but despite that, they stay 
strong and try their best...

255
00:12:56.630 --> 00:13:00.980
These girls shine brightest within a game!

256
00:13:03.840 --> 00:13:07.830
There's a girl who I want 
to star in her own game.

257
00:13:08.590 --> 00:13:12.470
I want her to go on a grand adventure!

258
00:13:13.390 --> 00:13:16.940
Which is why I want it to be a game, 
and not just illustrations.

259
00:13:16.940 --> 00:13:22.250
Bishojo games are where cute 
girls can truly come alive!

260
00:13:23.200 --> 00:13:27.470
I don't know much about video games,

261
00:13:27.470 --> 00:13:32.630
but I'm sure that any game you 
make would be very fun to play.

262
00:13:39.150 --> 00:13:42.780
Granny!

263
00:13:40.980 --> 00:13:43.290
Goodness, what's wrong?

264
00:13:43.290 --> 00:13:47.010
No one at work will listen 
to what I have to say.

265
00:13:47.010 --> 00:13:49.140
I'm just as aware as everyone else!

266
00:13:49.140 --> 00:13:51.630
Our company could never 
make a full-priced game!

267
00:13:52.110 --> 00:13:58.280
Even so, I just want someone to hear 
me out a little, just a little!

268
00:14:00.930 --> 00:14:04.690
Games are supposed to be fun 
and fill you with excitement...

269
00:14:05.040 --> 00:14:08.700
But no one at our company dares to dream!

270
00:14:09.360 --> 00:14:12.510
A game that doesn't dare to 
dream isn't a game at all!

271
00:14:12.510 --> 00:14:14.060
I don't care if it's a game about hypnosis!

272
00:14:14.060 --> 00:14:16.870
I want to make a game that dares to dream!

273
00:14:19.080 --> 00:14:22.410
And you can't stop working at that company?

274
00:14:22.410 --> 00:14:24.430
Well, um...

275
00:14:24.430 --> 00:14:27.990
I don't have it in me to be so assertive...

276
00:14:27.990 --> 00:14:32.430
Quitting would be too scary, so that's 
gonna be a no sirree from me...

277
00:14:32.430 --> 00:14:34.090
Dearie me...

278
00:14:36.420 --> 00:14:42.290
But thanks to you, it feels like I 
managed to shake off some of my gloom!

279
00:14:42.290 --> 00:14:45.510
Um, may I come back here?

280
00:14:45.510 --> 00:14:46.990
Yes, of course.

281
00:14:46.990 --> 00:14:50.150
Feel free to visit whenever we're open.

282
00:14:51.110 --> 00:14:53.310
Thanks, granny!

283
00:15:07.630 --> 00:15:12.030
<i>Maybe I'll stop by that BiBi game 
store I found during lunch.</i>

284
00:15:13.340 --> 00:15:15.040
Thank you very much!

